  "original_title": "Sri Lanka to develop power reform plan in a month: Minister",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka to develop power reform plan in a month: Minister",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 A framework to reform Sri Lanka\u2019s state-run Ceylon Electricity Board will be developed within a month, Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera has said.",
        "A reform committee has been appointed to come up with a plan.",
        "The committee has already met with development agencies, sector experts and will meet political parties and the regulator next week.",
        "\u201cThe main framework will be presented to the cabinet of ministers by the end of the month,\u201d he said in a twitter.com message.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s CEB, which is a government owned monopoly has been partially split under an \u2018unbundling\u2019 plan developed 20 years ago while a part of the generation is privately owned.",
        "However due to the regulator not raising prices, the CEB is running losses. From 2013 when prices were cut, to 2022, the rupee has fallen from 130 to around 360. (Colombo/Sept04/2022)"
      ],
